# Plan lifecycle

- New execution-ready plans belong in `docs/plans/active/`.
- Plans that are partially implemented, blocked, stale, or need verification belong in `docs/plans/review-needed/`.
- Fully executed or superseded plans belong in `docs/plans/archived/`.
- Keep only one canonical copy of a plan. Do not leave duplicate plan notes across root folders.
- When a plan changes status, update:
  - `docs/plans/README.md`
  - `docs/architecture/agent-roadmap-and-handoff.md`
  - the local README in the destination folder
- During migration, if older numbered plans still physically live in `docs/plans/`, treat `docs/architecture/agent-roadmap-and-handoff.md` as the status source of truth.
